The New Testament was translated into the [[Nepali language]] in 1821 by [[William Carey (missionary)|Carey]]'s [[Serampore]] mission. The complete Bible was translated by [[Newar people|Newari]] pastor [[Ganga Prasad Pradhan]] in 1914.

In 2010, the New Testament of [[New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures]] was released by [[Jehovah's Witnesses]] in Nepali.<ref>"WatchTower publications", Watchtower publications Index (1986-2016)</ref> It was [https://wol.jw.org/ne/wol/binav/r56/lp-np/bi7/NP/2010 published online] (also offline in [https://download-a.akamaihd.net/files/media_bible/95/bi7_NP.pdf PDF format]) with mobile versions released through ''JW Library'' application in App stores.

In 2018, complete [[New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures]] was released by [[Jehovah's Witnesses]] in Nepali.<ref>[https://www.jw.org/en/whats-new/bible-ecuadorian-sign-language-nepali News Release on jw.org]</ref> It is available on [https://www.jw.org/ne/प्रकाशनहरू/बाइबल jw.org], [https://wol.jw.org/ne/wol/binav/r56/lp-np/nwt/NP/2018 Watchtower Online Library] and through ''JW Library'' application in App stores.

