{{Unreferenced|date=September 2007}}

'''Blowback''' in [[forensics]] refers to [[vacuum]] effect created in the [[Gun barrel|barrel]] of a [[firearm]] when it is discharged.

After the [[weapon]] is fired, [[air]] races into the barrel once the [[bullet]] has left the muzzle. This vacuum can pull in trace amounts of materials from the environment.

[[Police]] can use [[blood]] and [[Biological tissue|tissue]] which have entered a gun barrel through blowback in an investigation.


[[Category:Firearm terminology]]


