This article deals with the [[phonology]] and [[phonetics]] of [[Standard Modern Greek]]. For phonological characteristics of other varieties, see [[varieties of Modern Greek]], and for Cypriot, specifically, see {{section link|Cypriot Greek|Phonology}}.

==Consonants==
Greek [[linguist]]s do not agree on which consonants to count as [[phoneme]]s in their own right, and which to count as conditional [[allophone]]s. The table below is adapted from {{harvtxt|Arvaniti|2007|p=7}}, who does away with the entire [[palatal consonant|palatal]] series, and both [[affricate consonant|affricate]]s {{IPAblink|t͡s}} and {{IPAblink|d͡z}}.

