|}

==Stress==
Unlike [[Ancient Greek]], which had a [[pitch accent]] system, Modern Greek has variable (phonologically unpredictable) [[stress (linguistics)|stress]]. Every multisyllabic word carries stress on one of its three final syllables. [[Enclitic]]s form a single [[phonological word]] together with the host word to which they attach, and count towards the three-syllable rule too. In these cases, primary stress shifts to the second-to-last syllable (e.g. {{lang|el|αυτοκίνητό μου}} {{IPA|[aftoˌciniˈto mu]}} 'my car'). Phonetically, stressed syllables are longer and/or carry higher amplitude.{{sfn|Arvaniti|1999|p=5}}

The position of the stress can vary between different inflectional forms of the same word within its inflectional paradigm. In some paradigms, the stress is always on the third last syllable, shifting its position in those forms that have longer affixes (e.g. {{lang|el|κάλεσα}} 'I called' vs. {{lang|el|καλέσαμε}} 'we called'; {{lang|el|πρόβλημα}} 'problem' vs. {{lang|el|προβλήματα}} 'problems'). In some word classes, stress position also preserves an older pattern inherited from [[Ancient Greek]], according to which a word could not be accented on the third-from-last syllable if the [[ultima (linguistics)|last syllable]] was long, e.g. {{lang|el|άνθρωπος}} ('man', [[nominative|nom.]] [[Grammatical number|sg.]], last syllable short), but {{lang|el|ανθρώπων}} ('of men', [[genitive case|gen.]] [[plural|pl.]], last syllable long). However, in Modern Greek this rule is no longer automatic and does not apply to all words (e.g. {{lang|el|καλόγερος}} 'monk', {{lang|el|καλόγερων}} 'of monks'), as the phonological length distinction itself no longer exists.{{sfn|Holton|Mackridge|Philippaki-Warburton|1998|pp=25–27, 53–54}}

==Sample==
This sample text, the first sentence of the [[Aesop's Fables|fable]] of [[The North Wind and the Sun]] in Greek, and the accompanying transcription are adapted from {{harvtxt|Arvaniti|1999|pp=5–6}}.

===Orthographic version===
{{lang|el|Ο βοριάς κι ο ήλιος μάλωναν για το ποιος απ’ τους δυο είναι ο δυνατότερος, όταν έτυχε να περάσει από μπροστά τους ένας ταξιδιώτης που φορούσε κάπα.}}

===Transcription===
{{IPA|[o voˈɾʝas ˈco̯iʎoz ˈmalonan {{pipe}} ʝa to ˈpços aptuz ˈðʝo ˈineo̯ ðinaˈtoteɾos {{pipe}} ˈota ˈnetiçe napeˈɾasi apo broˈstatus {{pipe}} ˈenas taksiˈðʝotis pu̥ foˈɾuse ˈkapa]}}

