{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}}
{{for|striking combinations in computer games| Combo (video gaming)}}

[[Image:Ouch-boxing-footwork.jpg|thumb|Punching combinations are an essential part of [[boxing]].]]

A '''striking combination''' (generally referred to as a '''combination''' or "'''combo'''") is a combination of [[strike (attack)|strikes]] performed in rapid succession, usually from a [[stand-up fighting|stand-up position]]. If the combination includes only [[punch (strike)|punches]], it is called a '''punching combination''', and if it includes only [[kick]]s, it is called a '''kicking combination'''.

Popular striking combinations consist of punches which allow the fighter to shift weight from one leg to the other in a natural rhythm.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://heavyfists.com/boxing-combinations | title=Top 5 most popular boxing combinations}}{{Dead link|date=October 2017|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>

